The room was spacious (for Paris standards, I have been in Parisian hotels where the rooms were as large as closets) and had a queen and bedsofa for the children.	Our queen executive room was spacious by Paris standards, clean, with a comfy bed but no feather pillows.	Breakfast was very good and overall a good value by Paris standards with a large selection.	It's clean and room's space is average for standard rooms (Executive rooms are better but they come with a significant extra price).	Went down and complain and were given a larger than standard executive room (one of those larger rooms in odd corner).